<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 428
                    The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations (
                        Pauley
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State
                    
                    Sent to the Acting Secretary of State over the
                        signature of Harriman.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d428</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">428</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-07T11:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-07T11:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-07T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="428" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/7–745:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 428<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pauley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d428fn1">Sent to the Acting Secretary of State over the
                        signature of <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-07T19:00:00+03:00">July 7, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2465. From <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName> for the Secretary.</p>
                <p>Concerning <persName>Potter Hyndley</persName> report<note n="2" xml:id="d428fn2">See enclosure 2 to <ref target="#d421">document No. 421</ref>.</note> on
                    coal situation I fully agree that immediate action should be taken to export
                    from Germany all coal in excess of German needs and to secure early attainment
                    of maximum production. (<gloss target="#t_reurtel1">Reurtel</gloss> 1500, July
                    3, 11 a.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d428fn3">
                        <ref target="#d424">Document No. 424</ref>.</note>)</p>
                <p>However, I feel that those countries that do not pay for the coal received should
                    be given definite notice that such coal deliveries may either be considered as
                    part of reparations payments when final reparation plan is put into effect or
                    considered exports for which payment in acceptable currencies will be
                    required.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
